🔋 POWER CONNECTIONS:

1. ESP8266 Power:

```
POWER BANK → USB Cable → NodeMCU USB Port
```

2. Battery Pack:

```
3x 18650 → Battery Holder → 3S BMS
BMS P+ → +11.1V OUTPUT
BMS P- → GND OUTPUT
```

🔥 MAIN IGNITION CIRCUIT:

3. High Current Path:

```
BMS P+ (11.1V) → 5A FUSE → NICHROME WIRE → MOSFET DRAIN (Pin 2)
MOSFET SOURCE (Pin 3) → BMS P- (GND)
```

🛡️ PROTECTION CIRCUIT:

4. Diode Connection:

```
1N4007 DIODE:
- CATHODE (Striped end) → MOSFET DRAIN
- ANODE → BMS P+ (11.1V)
```

🎛️ CONTROL CIRCUIT:

5. MOSFET Control:

```
NodeMCU D1 → 220Ω RESISTOR → MOSFET GATE (Pin 1)
MOSFET GATE → 10K RESISTOR → BMS P- (GND)
```

🔗 COMMON GROUND (CRITICAL):

6. Ground Connections:

```
NodeMCU GND → BMS P- (GND)
[ALL GNDs CONNECTED TOGETHER]
```

📍 PIN-TO-PIN CONNECTIONS:

NodeMCU:

· D1 → 220Ω → MOSFET GATE
· GND → BMS P- (GND)
· USB → Power Bank

MOSFET IRF3205:

· GATE (Pin 1) → 220Ω from D1 + 10K to GND
· DRAIN (Pin 2) → Nichrome from BMS P+
· SOURCE (Pin 3) → BMS P- (GND)

BMS:

· P+ → Fuse → Nichrome
· P- → MOSFET SOURCE + NodeMCU GND + 10K Resistor

⚡ CIRCUIT OPERATION:

When IGNITE Command:

1. Web interface → "IGNITE" click
2. NodeMCU D1 goes HIGH (3.3V)
3. MOSFET GATE gets voltage → Turns ON
4. Current flows: Battery → Fuse → Nichrome → MOSFET → GND
5. Nichrome heats up (4 seconds)
6. Auto cutoff → MOSFET OFF

🎯 VISUAL CIRCUIT FLOW:

```
POWER BANK → NodeMCU USB
    ↓
BMS P+ → FUSE → NICHROME → MOSFET DRAIN → MOSFET SOURCE → BMS P-
    ↑              ↓               ↓        ↓
    └── DIODE ←────┘               │        │
    ↑                              │        │
    └── 10K ←── GATE ←── 220Ω ←── D1       │
    ↓                                      │
    └── COMMON GND ←── NodeMCU GND ←───────┘
```

⚠️ SAFETY CHECKLIST:

· ✅ FUSE installed in series with BMS P+
· ✅ DIODE correct direction (Striped to DRAIN)
· ✅ COMMON GND connected
· ✅ All connections tight and secure
· ✅ Battery polarity correct

🔧 TESTING SEQUENCE:

1. Power Test:

· Power Bank → NodeMCU → Blue LED on
· Battery → BMS → Output voltage check (11.1V)

2. WiFi Test:

· Connect to "Biswajit_Igniter" WiFi
· Open 192.168.4.1 in browser
· Web interface show

3. Control Test:

· Web interface → "INSTANT" mode → "IGNITE"
· MOSFET should activate for 4 seconds

4. Full Test:

· Connect nichrome → Short ignition test
· Nichrome should glow red hot

🎯 CIRCUIT COMPLETE! READY FOR DEPLOYMENT! 🔥
